def load_food_access_data():
    """
    Loads and preprocess the Food Access Research Atlas dataset
    """
    
    file_path = os.path.join(data_dir, 'FoodAccessResearchAtlasData2019.xlsx')
    fara_data = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Food Access Research Atlas')
    ca_data = fara_data[fara_data['State'] == 'California']
    print(f"Filtered to {len(ca_data)} census tracts in California")
    return ca_data

def load_census_tracts():
    """
    Loads California census tract boundaries
    """
    
    census_file = os.path.join(data_dir, 'ca_census_tracts.shp')
    tracts = gpd.read_file(census_file)
    print(f"Loaded {len(tracts)} census tract boundaries")
    return tracts

def load_tribal_areas():
    """
    Loads California tribal areas
    """
    
    tribal_file = os.path.join(data_dir, 'ca_tribal_areas.shp')
    print("Loading California tribal areas...")
    tribal = gpd.read_file(tribal_file)
    print(f"Loaded {len(tribal)} tribal areas")
    return tribal

def merge_data(ca_fa_data, ca_tracts, ca_tribal_areas):
    """
    Merges food access data w/ spatial boundaries from ca_census_tracts and ca_tribal_areas
    """    
    
    # Merge based on Census Tract ID
    ca_fa_data['CensusTract'] = ca_fa_data['CensusTract'].astype(str).str.zfill(11)
    ca_tracts['GEOID10'] = ca_tracts['GEOID10'].astype(str)
    merged_data = ca_tracts.merge(ca_fa_data, left_on='GEOID10', right_on='CensusTract', how='right')
        
    # Ensure coordinate systems match
    ca_tribal_areas = ca_tribal_areas.to_crs(merged_data.crs)
    merged_data = merged_data.reset_index(drop=True)
    
    # Join all geographically intersecting geometries
    intersects = gpd.sjoin(
        merged_data,
        ca_tribal_areas,
        how='left',
        predicate='intersects'
    )
    
    intersects['is_tribal'] = ~intersects['index_right'].isna()
    
    # Count unique tribal census tracts using the CensusTract column
    unique_tribal_tracts = intersects[intersects['is_tribal']]['CensusTract'].nunique()
    print(f"Identified {unique_tribal_tracts} unique tribal census tracts")
    
    # Raw count
    raw_tribal_count = intersects['is_tribal'].sum()
    print(f"Raw count of tribal intersections: {raw_tribal_count}")
    intersects_no_dups = intersects.drop_duplicates(subset=['CensusTract'])
    print(f"After removing duplicates: {len(intersects_no_dups)} records")
    
    return intersects_no_dups 
    
merged_data = merge_data(ca_fa_data, ca_tracts, ca_tribal_areas);

def create_food_desert_map(merged_data, output_dir):    
    """
    Creates a map that outlines tribal areas and highlights food deserts
    """

    # https://www.ers.usda.gov/data-products/food-access-research-atlas/documentation#lowaccess
    
    # Definition 1: half-mile urban, 10-mile rural
    merged_data['is_food_desert_def1'] = merged_data['LILATracts_halfAnd10'] == 1
    
    # Definition 2: 1-mile urban, 10-mile rural (most common)
    merged_data['is_food_desert_def2'] = merged_data['LILATracts_1And10'] == 1
    
    # Definition 3: 1-mile urban, 20-mile rural
    merged_data['is_food_desert_def3'] = merged_data['LILATracts_1And20'] == 1
    
    # Definition 4: Vehicle access
    merged_data['is_food_desert_def4'] = merged_data['LILATracts_Vehicle'] == 1
    
    # Comprehensive definition (any of the above)
    merged_data['is_food_desert'] = (
        merged_data['is_food_desert_def1'] | 
        merged_data['is_food_desert_def2'] | 
        merged_data['is_food_desert_def3'] | 
        merged_data['is_food_desert_def4']
    )
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 15))
    
    food_deserts = merged_data[merged_data['is_food_desert']]
    food_deserts.plot(color='lightcoral', ax=ax, linewidth=0.1, edgecolor='gray', label='Food Desert')
    
    non_food_deserts = merged_data[~merged_data['is_food_desert']]
    non_food_deserts.plot(color='lightgray', ax=ax, linewidth=0.1, edgecolor='gray', label='Not Food Desert')
    
    merged_data[merged_data['is_tribal']].boundary.plot(ax=ax, color='blue', linewidth=1.0, label='Tribal Area Boundaries')
    
    # Custom legend (needed to handle GeoPandas PatchCollection)
    from matplotlib.patches import Patch
    legend_elements = [
        Patch(facecolor='lightcoral', label='Food Desert'),
        Patch(facecolor='lightgray', label='Not Food Desert'),
        Patch(facecolor='white', edgecolor='blue', linewidth=1.0, label='Tribal Area Boundaries')
    ]
    ax.legend(handles=legend_elements, loc='upper right', title='Food Access Categories')
    ax.axis('off')  
    plt.title('Food Deserts and Tribal Areas in California', fontsize=16)
    plt.tight_layout()

    output_file = os.path.join(output_dir, 'ca_food_deserts_tribal_areas.png')
    plt.savefig(output_file, dpi=300)    

create_food_desert_map(merged_data, output_dir)

def create_vehicle_access_map(merged_data, output_dir):
    """
    Creates a map that outlines tribal areas and shows vehicle access issues,
    using TractHUNV (~2015-2019 ACS) / OHU2010 (2010 Census) and capping the
    resulting percentage at 100. Colorbar max is capped at 50.
    """

    merged_data['pct_no_vehicle'] = (merged_data['TractHUNV'] / merged_data['OHU2010']) * 100
    merged_data['pct_no_vehicle'] = merged_data['pct_no_vehicle'].fillna(merged_data['pct_no_vehicle'].median())


    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 15))

    merged_data.plot(
        column='pct_no_vehicle',
        linewidth=0.1,
        ax=ax,
        cmap='plasma_r',
        edgecolor='gray',
        legend=True,
        vmin=0,
        vmax=50, 
        legend_kwds={'label': f"% Households Without Vehicle Access (Scale capped at {50}%)", 
                     'orientation': "horizontal"} 
    )

    merged_data[merged_data['is_tribal']].boundary.plot(ax=ax, color='blue', linewidth=1.0, label='Tribal Area Boundaries')
    
    legend_elements = [
        Patch(facecolor='none', edgecolor='blue', linewidth=1.0, label='Tribal Area Boundaries')
    ]
    ax.legend(handles=legend_elements, loc='upper right')
    ax.axis('off')      
    plt.title('Vehicle Access Issues and Tribal Areas in California\n(% Households w/o Vehicle, Color Scale Capped at 50%)', fontsize=16)
    plt.tight_layout()

    output_file = os.path.join(output_dir, 'ca_vehicle_access_tribal_areas.png')
    plt.savefig(output_file, dpi=300)

create_vehicle_access_map(merged_data, output_dir)

def create_supermarket_access_map(merged_data, output_dir):
    """
    Creates a map showing selected USDA-defined low-access census tracts,
    focusing on key definitions and general access issues, with tribal area highlights.
    """
    
    conditions = [
        # Definition 2: 1 mile urban, 10 mile rural (LILATracts_1And10)
        (merged_data['LILATracts_1And10'] == 1),
        # Definition 4: Vehicle access (LILATracts_Vehicle)
        (merged_data['LILATracts_Vehicle'] == 1),
        # General distance measures (without income consideration)
        (merged_data['LATracts1'] == 1),
        (merged_data['LATracts10'] == 1),
    ]
    
    choices = [
        'Low-income & low-access (1 mile urban/10 mile rural)',
        'Low-income & vehicle-limited access',
        'General access issue (1 mile urban)',
        'General access issue (10 mile rural)'
    ]
    merged_data['access_category'] = np.select(
        conditions, 
        choices, 
        default='Adequate supermarket access'
    )
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 16))
    merged_data.plot(
        color='lightgray', 
        ax=ax, 
        linewidth=0.2, 
        edgecolor='gray', 
    )
    merged_data[merged_data['is_tribal']].boundary.plot(ax=ax, color='blue', linewidth=1.0, label='Tribal Area Boundaries')   
    
    access_colors = {
        'Low-income & low-access (1 mile urban/10 mile rural)': 'orange',  
        'Low-income & vehicle-limited access': 'red',                   
        'General access issue (1 mile urban)': 'gold',                  
        'General access issue (10 mile rural)': 'lightpink',       
    }
    for category, color in access_colors.items():
        subset = merged_data[merged_data['access_category'] == category]
        subset.plot(
            color=color,
            ax=ax,
            linewidth=0.3,
            edgecolor='gray',
            label=category
        )
    
    legend_elements = [
        Patch(facecolor='red', label='Low-income + 1mi urban/10mi rural (USDA Def2)'),
        Patch(facecolor='orange', label='Low-income + vehicle access limited (USDA Def4)'),
        Patch(facecolor='gold', label='General 1mi urban access issue'),
        Patch(facecolor='lightpink', label='General 10mi rural access issue'),
        Patch(facecolor='lightgray', label='Adequate access areas'),
        Patch(facecolor='white', edgecolor='blue', label='Tribal Areas')
    ]
    ax.legend(
        handles=legend_elements,
        loc='upper right',
        title='Supermarket Access Categories',
        fontsize=10,
        title_fontsize=12
    )
    
    plt.title(
        'Key USDA-Identified Low Supermarket Access Areas in California\n'
        'Focusing on Primary Access Measures',
        fontsize=16,
    )
    
    ax.axis('off')
    plt.tight_layout()
    output_file = os.path.join(output_dir, 'ca_supermarket_access_key_measures.png')
    plt.savefig(output_file, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')

create_supermarket_access_map(merged_data, output_dir)
